# {{CMD_PREFIX}}-continue

Model/effort: Sonnet / medium.

The default driver of forward progress. Runs the full open ritual, takes the
highest-priority unclaimed backlog item, does the work on a branch, and lands it
via PR with the close ritual.

## Steps
1. OPEN ritual: read the operating contract, the latest `05-logs/` entry, and the
   master index; fetch and prune; check for overlap; set model + effort to fit the
   work; state the objective.
2. Pick the top unclaimed backlog item; self-assign the issue and set it in progress.
3. Create and push a branch early (`feat/<issue>-slug` or `fix/<issue>-slug`) as a
   visible claim; record it in the active-agents registry.
4. Do the work. Commit and push after every commit. Run the test suite the way the
   project runs it before opening the PR.
5. Open a PR targeting `main`; ensure CI is green.
6. CLOSE ritual: append a continuity entry to `05-logs/<date>-<topic>.md`; update the
   decision board if anything changed; regenerate the capabilities map and validate
   the docs mesh; update board/issue/PR state; push everything.

## Done when
The PR is open with green CI, the continuity entry is written, the capabilities map
is current, and the claim is cleared on merge.
